Parallel correlation-based pseudo-amino-acid composition (PC-PseAAC) measures the parallel correlation between any two amino acids in a protein sequence [13]. For a given strain P, the PC-PseAAC feature vector is represented by
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
